'''Anatoly Konstantinovich Rozhdestvensky''' ({{lang-ru|Анатолий Константинович Рождественский}}, 1920–1983) was a Russian paleontologist responsible for naming many dinosaurs, including ''[[Aralosaurus]]'' and ''[[Probactrosaurus]]''.


