{{notable|date=January 2018}}
The [[Project Gemini|Gemini]] spacecraft was the first American craft that could dock to another in space.

It used a non-androgynous docking mechanism.

The docking system was not hollow, so there was no ability to transfer people or material between the craft; the docking system merely locked two craft together.

