'''Trevor Hatherton''' {{post-nominals|country=NZL|OBE|size=85%}} (30 September 1924 – 2 May 1992) was a New Zealand geophysicist, scientific administrator and Antarctic scientist. He was born in [[Sharlston]], Yorkshire, England on 30 September 1924.<ref name="DNZB Hatherton">{{DNZB|title=Trevor Hatherton|first= James W.|last= Brodie|id=5h10|accessdate=5 February 2012}}</ref>

In the [[1958 Birthday Honours|1958 Queen's Birthday Honours]] Hatherton was appointed an [[Order of the British Empire|Officer of the Order of the British Empire]].<ref>{{London Gazette |issue=41406 |date=12 June 1958 |page=3554 |supp=y }}</ref>

