'''Dr. Xiaobo Yu''' is a Chinese [[palaeontology|palaeontologist]] and professor on [[biological sciences]]. Yu is credited with first describing the lobe-finned fish ''[[Psarolepis]]'' romeri, a transitional species between fish and amphibians. Yu is currently a professor at [[Kean University]] in Union, New Jersey.

==References==
{{reflist}}
* Yu, Xiaobo (June 1998). "A new porolepiform-like fish, Psarolepis romeri, gen. et sp. nov. (Sarcopterygii, Osteichthyes) from the Lower Devonian of Yunnan, China". Journal of Vertebrate Paleontology 18 (2): 261–274.

